snippet.title: MUST SEE Barron Trump and Taylor Swift sing "Anchor In The Storm"
snippet.description:
Anchor In The Storm

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics:
(Verse 1 – Barron)
When I was lost and walking blind,
No peace or truth that I could find.
But then His light broke through the gray,
And Jesus showed me a better way.

(Verse 2 – Taylor Swift)
I’ve run through nights with tear-stained eyes,
Chased every dream beneath the skies.
But nothing fills the ache inside,
Like mercy that will never hide.

(Chorus – Both)
Jesus, You’re the anchor in the storm,
The steady hand, the grace that keeps me warm.
In every high, in every low,
You're the only love I'll ever know.

(Verse 3 – Barron)
I’ve seen the world, its highs and falls,
But still I hear Your gentle calls.
You’re not a myth, You’re not a name—
You're the reason that I’m changed.

(Verse 4 – Taylor Swift)
They tried to tell me hope was gone,
But You were there all along.
In every whisper, every song,
You were the strength that pulled me on.

(Chorus – Both)
Jesus, You’re the anchor in the storm,
The steady hand, the grace that keeps me warm.
In every high, in every low,
You're the only love I'll ever know.

(Bridge – Both)
When the world fades and lights grow dim,
I’ll lift my hands and trust in Him.
Through every trial, through every flame,
I’ll praise the power of His name.

(Final Chorus – Both)
Jesus, You’re the anchor in the storm,
The steady hand, the grace that keeps me warm.
Forevermore, in You I’ll stay—
My Savior, light, and only way.
